{
  "texts": [
    "Kanwal et al. (2011) introduce a novel approach by proposing adaptive neighborhoods, significantly enhancing fine details in X-ray images, and addressing low contrast in X-ray images caused by fluids in the human body.",
    "This technique can enhance contrast in fossil images across various modalities, including SEM and noise-prone CT scans.",
    "Similarly, noise reduction techniques, such as wavelet transformations, play a crucial role in diminishing interference in ultrasound imagery.",
    "Choi et al. (2015) present a discrete wavelet transform (DWT) and an image fusion technique to improve ultrasound image quality by reducing speckle noise.",
    "This principle can be applied to SEM, CT and thin-section fossil images to eliminate granular noise, thereby improving the accuracy of the performance of ML/DL models employed for fossil analysis."
  ]
}